<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-20T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="513" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d513">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">339.115 General Motors Export Co./159:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-20T19:00:00-04:00">May 20, 1935—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>28. Your 71 May 20, 1 p.m.<note n="25" xml:id="d513fn25">Not
                                printed.</note> You are authorized to urge President Trujillo to
                            withdraw charges against Barletta, making appropriate <pb facs="0596" n="503" xml:id="pg_503"/> reference to my statements to the
                            Dominican Minister as reported in Department’s 25 May 14, 7 p.m. and to
                            the fact that American interests are sustaining injury as the result of
                            Barletta’s continued imprisonment.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>